<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-31T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-31T10:00:00-05:00" n="114" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4774: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-31T16:00:00+01:00">July 31, 1931—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 31—11 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>283. From Gibson. The Committee of Experts has decided to hold a
                                recess until the 11th of August, leaving the preparation and
                                circulation of texts up to a drafting committee, and allowing time
                                for conversations between the Governments. We hope that a very short
                                plenary session will be sufficient.</p>
                            <p>Hearings with respect to the problem of Near Eastern reparations will
                                be held by another subcommittee, which will try to have a plan ready
                                for consideration on August 11th at the plenary meeting.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>